00:45:22.360 --> 00:45:25.860
Then came together unto him the Pharisees

00:45:25.860 --> 00:45:29.100
and certain of the scribes, which came from Jerusalem.

00:45:29.640 --> 00:45:33.560
And when they saw some of his disciples eat bread

00:45:33.560 --> 00:45:38.640
with defiled, that is to say, with unwashing hands,

00:45:38.920 --> 00:45:40.180
they found fault.

00:45:40.520 --> 00:45:42.760
For the Pharisees and all the Jews,

00:45:43.120 --> 00:45:47.700
except they wash their hands oft,

00:45:47.700 --> 00:45:52.280
eat not, holding the traditions of the elders.

00:45:52.840 --> 00:45:56.160
And when they come from the market, except they wash,

00:45:56.420 --> 00:45:59.540
they eat not, and many other things there be,

00:45:59.860 --> 00:46:04.100
which they have received, to hold as the washing of cups

00:46:04.100 --> 00:46:07.780
and pots, brazen vessels and of tables.

00:46:08.240 --> 00:46:11.540
Then the Pharisees and scribes asked him,

00:46:11.940 --> 00:46:15.040
Why walk not thy disciples according

00:46:15.040 --> 00:46:17.780
to the traditions of the elders,

00:46:18.200 --> 00:46:21.340
but eat bread with unwashing hands?

00:46:21.680 --> 00:46:24.120
He answered and said unto them,

00:46:24.540 --> 00:46:28.100
Well, Hathisias prophesied of you hypocrites,

00:46:28.540 --> 00:46:32.260
as it is written, this people honoreth me with their lips,

00:46:32.620 --> 00:46:35.040
but their hearts are far from me.

00:46:35.660 --> 00:46:38.600
Howbeit in vain do they worship me,

00:46:38.620 --> 00:46:42.520
teaching for doctrines the commandments of men.

00:46:43.230 --> 00:46:45.760
For laying aside the commandment of God,

00:46:46.100 --> 00:46:49.720
ye hold the tradition of men as the washing of pots

00:46:49.720 --> 00:46:53.800
and cups, and many other such like things ye do.

00:46:54.120 --> 00:46:57.200
And he said unto them, full well,

00:46:57.560 --> 00:46:59.580
ye reject the commandment of God,

00:47:00.240 --> 00:47:02.300
that ye may keep your own tradition.

00:47:03.000 --> 00:47:07.260
For Moses said, honor thy father and thy mother,

00:47:07.640 --> 00:47:10.360
and whoso curseth, father or mother,

00:47:10.360 --> 00:47:12.660
and let him die the death.

00:47:13.320 --> 00:47:17.000
But ye say, if a man shall say to his father or mother,

00:47:17.400 --> 00:47:19.900
it is Corbin, that is to say a gift,

00:47:20.260 --> 00:47:23.100
by whatsoever thou mightest be profited by me,

00:47:23.420 --> 00:47:24.740
he shall be free.

00:47:25.060 --> 00:47:29.400
And ye suffer him no more to do art for his father

00:47:29.400 --> 00:47:33.960
or his mother, making the word of God of non-effect

00:47:33.960 --> 00:47:37.620
through your tradition, which ye have delivered,

00:47:37.620 --> 00:47:41.000
and many such like things do ye.

00:47:41.560 --> 00:47:45.040
And when he had called all the people unto him,

00:47:45.440 --> 00:47:48.720
he said unto them, hearken unto me,

00:47:48.900 --> 00:47:51.460
every one of you, and understand,

00:47:52.040 --> 00:47:55.200
there is nothing from without a man

00:47:55.200 --> 00:47:58.580
that entering into him can defile him.

00:47:58.940 --> 00:48:01.860
But the things which come out of him,

00:48:01.980 --> 00:48:05.380
those are they that defile the man.

00:48:05.380 --> 00:48:10.700
If any man have ears to hear, let him hear.

00:48:11.240 --> 00:48:16.160
And when he was entered into the house from the people,

00:48:16.320 --> 00:48:20.120
his disciples asked him concerning the parable,

00:48:20.540 --> 00:48:25.860
and he sayeth unto them, are ye so without understanding also?

00:48:26.340 --> 00:48:30.700
Do ye not perceive that whatsoever thing from without

00:48:30.700 --> 00:48:34.300
entereth into the man, it cannot defile him,

00:48:34.300 --> 00:48:39.060
because it entereth not into his heart, but into the belly,

00:48:39.480 --> 00:48:43.900
and goeth out into the draught, purging all meats.

00:48:44.620 --> 00:48:48.620
And he said, that which cometh out of the man,

00:48:48.820 --> 00:48:52.340
that defileth the man, for from within,

00:48:52.740 --> 00:48:55.820
out of the heart of men proceed evil thoughts,

00:48:56.200 --> 00:49:00.820
adulteries, fornications, murders, thefts,

00:49:00.820 --> 00:49:05.240
covetousness, wickedness, deceit, lasciviousness,

00:49:05.440 --> 00:49:09.800
an evil eye, blasphemy, pride, foolishness,

00:49:09.960 --> 00:49:15.460
all these evil things come from within and defile the man.

00:49:15.820 --> 00:49:20.220
And from thence he arose and went into the borders of Tyre

00:49:20.690 --> 00:49:24.080
and Sedan, and entered into in house,

00:49:24.380 --> 00:49:29.280
and would have no man know it, but he could not behead.

00:49:29.740 --> 00:49:33.840
For a certain woman whose daughter had an unclean spirit

00:49:33.840 --> 00:49:37.200
heard of him and came and fell at his feet.

00:49:38.200 --> 00:49:42.060
The woman was a Greek, a Syriac Phoenician by nation,

00:49:42.480 --> 00:49:46.240
and she besought him that he would cast forth the devil

00:49:46.240 --> 00:49:47.600
out of her daughter.

00:49:48.280 --> 00:49:52.340
But Jesus said unto her, let the children first be filled,

00:49:52.740 --> 00:49:55.760
for it is not me to take the children's bread

00:49:55.760 --> 00:49:58.660
and to cast it unto the dogs.

00:49:59.280 --> 00:50:02.860
And she answered and said unto him, yes, Lord,

00:50:03.180 --> 00:50:07.180
yet the dogs under the table eat of the children's crumbs.

00:50:07.940 --> 00:50:11.960
And he said unto her, for this saying, go thy way,

00:50:12.260 --> 00:50:14.760
the devil is gone out of thy daughter.

00:50:15.360 --> 00:50:17.680
And when she was come to her house,

00:50:18.060 --> 00:50:20.060
she found the devil gone out,

00:50:20.060 --> 00:50:22.920
and her daughter laid upon the bed.

00:50:23.320 --> 00:50:28.000
And again, departing from the coast of Tyre and Sedan,

00:50:28.000 --> 00:50:31.040
he came unto the sea of Galilee

00:50:31.040 --> 00:50:34.220
through the midst of the coast of Decapolis.

00:50:34.500 --> 00:50:38.320
And they bring unto him one that was deaf

00:50:38.320 --> 00:50:40.880
and had an impediment in his speech,

00:50:41.200 --> 00:50:44.280
and they beseech him to put his hand upon him.

00:50:44.500 --> 00:50:47.660
And he took him aside from the multitude

00:50:47.660 --> 00:50:50.500
and put his fingers into his ears,

00:50:50.660 --> 00:50:53.600
and he spat and touched his tongue.

00:50:53.860 --> 00:50:57.320
And looking up to heaven, he sighed,

00:50:57.320 --> 00:51:03.960
and saith unto him, ifah, father, that is, be opened.

00:51:04.400 --> 00:51:06.800
And straightway his ears were opened,

00:51:07.160 --> 00:51:09.820
and the string of his tongue was loosed,

00:51:09.820 --> 00:51:11.200
and he spake plain.

00:51:11.760 --> 00:51:14.940
And he charged them that they should tell no man,

00:51:15.360 --> 00:51:18.180
but the more he charged them so much,

00:51:18.500 --> 00:51:21.600
the more a great deal they published it.

00:51:21.980 --> 00:51:25.180
And were beyond measure astonished,

00:51:25.180 --> 00:51:28.380
saying he hath done all things well,

00:51:28.940 --> 00:51:33.600
he maketh both the deaf to hear and the dumb to speak.

00:51:37.320 --> 00:51:38.980
In those days the multitude,

00:51:39.340 --> 00:51:42.200
being very great and having nothing to eat,

00:51:42.600 --> 00:51:45.120
Jesus called his disciples unto him,

00:51:45.560 --> 00:51:50.440
and saith unto them, I have compassion on the multitude,

00:51:51.000 --> 00:51:54.700
because they have now been with me three days,

00:51:54.700 --> 00:51:56.720
and have nothing to eat.

00:51:57.420 --> 00:52:00.860
And if I send them away fasting to their own houses,

00:52:01.240 --> 00:52:03.220
they will faint by the way,

00:52:03.620 --> 00:52:06.820
for divers of them came from far.

00:52:07.280 --> 00:52:10.700
And his disciples answered him, from whence?

00:52:10.860 --> 00:52:14.580
Can a man satisfy these men with bread here

00:52:14.580 --> 00:52:15.800
in the wilderness?

00:52:16.160 --> 00:52:19.240
And he asked them, how many loaves have ye?

00:52:19.640 --> 00:52:21.420
And they said, seven.

00:52:21.740 --> 00:52:25.980
And he commanded the people to sit down on the ground,

00:52:26.320 --> 00:52:29.660
and he took the seven loaves and gave thanks and break,

00:52:30.200 --> 00:52:32.960
and gave to his disciples to set before them.

00:52:33.200 --> 00:52:36.040
And they did set them before the people,

00:52:36.380 --> 00:52:39.120
and they had a few small fish,

00:52:39.360 --> 00:52:43.980
and he blessed and commanded to set them also before them.

00:52:44.400 --> 00:52:47.760
So they did eat and were filled,

00:52:47.760 --> 00:52:50.720
and they took up of the broken meat

00:52:50.720 --> 00:52:53.780
that was left seven baskets.

00:52:54.660 --> 00:52:59.040
And they that had eaten were about 4,000,

00:52:59.260 --> 00:53:01.500
and he sent them away.

00:53:01.940 --> 00:53:05.880
And straightway he entered into a ship with his disciples,

00:53:06.320 --> 00:53:11.100
and came into the parts of Doumanutha.

00:53:11.300 --> 00:53:15.660
And the Pharisees came forth and began to question with him,

00:53:15.660 --> 00:53:19.660
seeking of him a sign from heaven, tempting him.

00:53:20.480 --> 00:53:23.720
And he sighed deeply in his spirit and saith,

00:53:24.100 --> 00:53:27.760
why doth this generation seek after a sign?

00:53:28.420 --> 00:53:32.300
Verily I say unto you, there shall no sign be given

00:53:32.300 --> 00:53:34.080
unto this generation.

00:53:34.400 --> 00:53:37.960
And he left them, and entering into the ship again,

00:53:38.260 --> 00:53:40.520
departed to the other side.

00:53:41.000 --> 00:53:44.100
Now the disciples had forgotten to take bread,

00:53:44.100 --> 00:53:49.000
neither had they in the ship with them more than one loaf.

00:53:49.660 --> 00:53:52.060
And he charged them saying, take heed,

00:53:52.640 --> 00:53:55.980
beware of the leaven of the Pharisees

00:53:55.980 --> 00:53:57.920
and of the leaven of Herod.

00:53:58.380 --> 00:54:00.720
And they reasoned among themselves saying,

00:54:01.040 --> 00:54:03.320
it is because we have no bread.

00:54:03.760 --> 00:54:06.680
And when Jesus knew it, he saith unto them,

00:54:07.100 --> 00:54:10.160
why reason ye because ye have no bread?

00:54:10.800 --> 00:54:14.020
Perceive ye not yet, neither understand?

00:54:14.700 --> 00:54:16.800
Have ye your heart yet hardened?

00:54:18.720 --> 00:54:21.420
Having eyes, see ye not?

00:54:21.740 --> 00:54:24.300
And having ears, hear ye not?

00:54:24.560 --> 00:54:28.400
And do ye not remember when I break the five loaves

00:54:28.400 --> 00:54:33.480
among 5,000, how many baskets full of fragments took ye up?

00:54:33.900 --> 00:54:36.200
They say unto him, 12.

00:54:36.700 --> 00:54:40.180
And when the seven among 4,000,

00:54:40.340 --> 00:54:44.060
how many baskets full of fragments took ye up?

00:54:44.260 --> 00:54:46.140
And they said, seven.

00:54:47.060 --> 00:54:51.560
And he said unto them, how is it that ye do not understand?

00:54:52.060 --> 00:54:54.800
And he cometh to Bethesda,

00:54:54.900 --> 00:54:57.620
and they bring a blind man unto him

00:54:57.620 --> 00:54:59.920
and besought him to touch him.

00:55:00.100 --> 00:55:03.720
And he took the blind man by the hand

00:55:03.720 --> 00:55:05.780
and led him out of the town.

00:55:05.980 --> 00:55:08.620
And when he had spit on his eyes

00:55:08.620 --> 00:55:11.200
and put his hands upon him,

00:55:11.200 --> 00:55:14.240
he asked him if he saw art.

00:55:14.740 --> 00:55:16.580
And he looked up and said,

00:55:16.880 --> 00:55:20.420
I see men as trees walking.

00:55:20.940 --> 00:55:24.720
After that, he put his hands again upon his eyes

00:55:24.720 --> 00:55:26.520
and made him look up.

00:55:26.680 --> 00:55:31.520
He was restored and saw every man clearly.

00:55:32.260 --> 00:55:35.300
And he sent him away to his house,

00:55:35.340 --> 00:55:38.000
saying, neither go into the town

00:55:38.000 --> 00:55:41.240
nor tell it to anyone in the town.

00:55:41.700 --> 00:55:44.360
And Jesus went out and his disciples

00:55:44.360 --> 00:55:47.480
into the towns of Caesarea Philippi.

00:55:47.740 --> 00:55:50.260
And by the way, he asked his disciples,

00:55:50.780 --> 00:55:55.780
saying unto them, whom do men say that I am?

00:55:56.160 --> 00:55:58.660
And they answered, John the Baptist.

00:55:59.020 --> 00:56:03.800
But some say Elias, others one of the prophets.

00:56:04.340 --> 00:56:06.020
And he sayeth unto them,

00:56:06.400 --> 00:56:08.900
but whom say ye that I am?

00:56:09.400 --> 00:56:12.340
And Peter answereth and sayeth unto him,

00:56:12.700 --> 00:56:14.500
thou art the Christ.

00:56:14.940 --> 00:56:19.080
And he charged them that they should tell no man of him.

00:56:19.400 --> 00:56:21.280
And he began to teach them

00:56:21.280 --> 00:56:25.560
that the son of man must suffer many things

00:56:25.560 --> 00:56:28.200
and be rejected of the elders

00:56:28.200 --> 00:56:32.460
and of the chief priests and scribes and be killed.

00:56:33.020 --> 00:56:36.260
And after three days rise again.

00:56:36.760 --> 00:56:40.100
And he spake that saying openly.

00:56:40.840 --> 00:56:43.580
And Peter took him and began to rebuke him.

00:56:43.880 --> 00:56:47.900
But when he had turned about and looked on his disciples,

00:56:48.000 --> 00:56:51.480
he rebuked Peter, saying, get thee behind me, Satan.

00:56:51.900 --> 00:56:54.440
For thou savoreth not the things of God,

00:56:54.440 --> 00:56:57.260
but the things that be of men.

00:56:57.960 --> 00:57:01.120
And when he had called the people unto him

00:57:01.120 --> 00:57:04.860
with his disciples also, he said unto them,

00:57:05.180 --> 00:57:07.440
whosoever will come after me,

00:57:07.780 --> 00:57:12.740
let him deny himself and take up his cross and follow me.

00:57:13.060 --> 00:57:16.960
For whosoever will save his life shall lose it.

00:57:17.160 --> 00:57:20.600
But whosoever shall lose his life for my sake

00:57:20.600 --> 00:57:24.180
in the gospels, the same shall save it.

00:57:24.580 --> 00:57:29.460
For what profit it a man if he shall gain the whole world

00:57:29.460 --> 00:57:32.280
and lose his own soul?

00:57:33.040 --> 00:57:36.580
Or what shall a man give in exchange for his soul?

00:57:37.880 --> 00:57:41.780
Whosoever therefore shall be ashamed of me

00:57:41.780 --> 00:57:47.260
and of my words in this adulterous and sinful generation

00:57:47.260 --> 00:57:51.140
of him also shall the son of man be ashamed

00:57:51.140 --> 00:57:54.640
when he cometh in the glory of his father

00:57:54.640 --> 00:57:57.160
with the holy angels.

00:58:54.760 --> 00:59:04.720
And leadeth them up into a high mountain, apart by themselves, and he was transfigured before them.

00:59:05.260 --> 00:59:14.880
And his raiment became shining, exceeding white as snow, so as no fuller on earth can white them.

00:59:15.460 --> 00:59:23.180
And there appeared unto them Elias with Moses, and they were talking with Jesus.

00:59:23.180 --> 00:59:31.420
And Peter answered and said to Jesus, Master, it is good for us to be here.

00:59:31.640 --> 00:59:40.240
And let us make three tabernacles, one for thee, and one for Moses, and one for Elias.

00:59:41.300 --> 00:59:46.640
For he wist not what to say, for they were sore afraid.

00:59:47.260 --> 00:59:54.200
And there was a cloud that overshadowed them, and a voice came out of the cloud, saying,

00:59:54.640 --> 00:59:58.540
This is my beloved Son, hear him.

00:59:59.260 --> 01:00:09.740
And suddenly, when they had looked around about, they saw no man any more, save Jesus only with themselves.

01:00:09.740 --> 01:00:22.340
And as they came down from the mountain, he charged them that they should tell no man what things they had seen till the Son of Man were risen from the dead.

01:00:23.160 --> 01:00:31.620
And they kept that saying with themselves, questioning one with another what the rising from the dead should mean.

01:00:31.620 --> 01:00:39.020
And they asked him, saying, Why say the scribes that Elias must first come?

01:00:39.580 --> 01:00:50.780
And he answered and told them, Elias fairly cometh first, and restoreth all things, and how it is written of the Son of Man,

01:00:50.780 --> 01:00:56.400
That he must suffer many things, and be set at naught.

01:00:57.060 --> 01:01:01.840
But I say unto you, that Elias is indeed come.

01:01:02.440 --> 01:01:09.580
And they have done unto him whatsoever they listed, as it is written of him.

01:01:09.580 --> 01:01:18.860
And when he came to his disciples, he saw a great multitude about them, and the scribes questioning with them.

01:01:19.220 --> 01:01:27.380
And straightway all the people when they beheld him were greatly amazed, and running to him, saluted him.

01:01:27.860 --> 01:01:31.960
And he asked the scribes, What question ye with them?

01:01:31.960 --> 01:01:42.380
And one of the multitude answered and said, Master, I have brought unto thee my son, which hath a dumb spirit.

01:01:42.900 --> 01:01:51.100
And wheresoever he taketh him, he terreth him, and he fometh and gnasheth with his teeth, and pineth away.

01:01:51.340 --> 01:01:57.840
And I spake to thy disciples that they should cast him out, and they could not.

01:01:57.840 --> 01:02:08.840
He answereth him, and saith, O faithless generation, How long shall I be with you? How long shall I suffer you?

01:02:09.240 --> 01:02:21.780
Bring him unto me. And they brought him to him. And when he saw him straightway the spirit tear him, and he fell on the ground, and wallowed foaming.

01:02:21.780 --> 01:02:39.500
And he asked his father, How long is it ago since this came unto him? And he said of a child, And oft times it has cast him into the fire and into the waters to destroy him.

01:02:39.500 --> 01:02:46.420
But if thou canst do anything, have compassion on us and help us.

01:02:47.100 --> 01:02:55.360
Jesus said unto him, If thou canst believe, all things are possible to him that believeth.

01:02:56.540 --> 01:03:05.740
And straightway the father of the child cried out and said with tears, Lord, I believe, help thou mine unbelief.

01:03:05.740 --> 01:03:20.040
When Jesus saw that the people came running together, he rebuked the foul spirit, saying unto him, Thou dumb and deaf spirit, I charge thee, come out of him, and enter no more into him.

01:03:20.040 --> 01:03:39.200
And the spirit cried, and rent him sore, and came out of him. And he was as one dead, in so much that many said he is dead. But Jesus took him by the hand and lifted him up, and he arose.

01:03:39.200 --> 01:03:56.540
And when he was come into the house, his disciples asked him privately, Why could not we cast him out? And he said unto them, This kind come forth by nothing but by prayer and fasting.

01:03:56.540 --> 01:04:14.320
And they departed thence and passed through Galilee, and he would not that any man should know it. For he taught his disciples and said unto them, The son of man is delivered into the hands of men, and they shall kill him.

01:04:14.320 --> 01:04:25.040
And after that he is killed, he shall rise the third day. But they understood not that saying, and were afraid to ask him.

01:04:25.040 --> 01:04:44.180
And he came to Capernaum, and being in the house, he asked them, What was it that ye disputed among yourselves by the way? But they held their peace, for by the way they had disputed among themselves, who should be the greatest?

01:04:44.180 --> 01:04:58.640
And he sat down and called the twelve, and saith unto them, If any man desire to be first, the same shall be last of all, and servant of all.

01:04:58.640 --> 01:05:14.720
And he took a child and set him in the midst of them. And when he had taken him in his arms, he said unto them, Whosoever shall receive one of such children in my name receiveth me.

01:05:14.720 --> 01:05:35.020
And whosoever shall receive me receiveth not me, but him that sent me. And John answered him, saying, Master, we saw one casting out devils in thy name, and he followeth not us, and we forbade him because he followeth not us.

01:05:35.020 --> 01:05:50.740
But Jesus said, Forbid him not, for there is no man which shall do a miracle in my name that can lightly speak evil of me. For he that is not against us is on our part.

01:05:50.740 --> 01:06:04.980
For whosoever shall give you a cup of water to drink in my name, because ye belong to Christ, verily I say unto you, he shall not lose his reward.

01:06:04.980 --> 01:06:19.960
And whosoever shall offend one of these little ones that believe in me, it is better for him that a millstone were hanged about his neck, and he were cast into the sea.

01:06:19.960 --> 01:06:44.100
And if thy hand offend thee, cut it off, it is better for thee to enter into life maimed than having two hands to go into hell, into the fire that never shall be quenched, where there worm dieth not, and the fire is not quenched.

01:06:44.100 --> 01:07:06.600
And if thy foot offend thee, cut it off, it is better for thee to enter, halt into life, than having two feet to be cast into hell, into the fire that never shall be quenched, where there worm dieth not, and the fire is not quenched.

01:07:06.600 --> 01:07:26.940
And if thine eye offend thee, pluck it out, it is better for thee to enter into the kingdom of God with one eye, than having two eyes to be cast into hell fire, where there worm dieth not, and the fire is not quenched.

01:07:26.940 --> 01:07:34.780
For every one shall be salted with fire, and every sacrifice shall be salted with salt.

01:07:35.780 --> 01:07:48.560
Salt is good, but if the salt have lost its saltness, wherewith will ye season it? Have salt in yourselves, and have peace one with another.

01:07:49.920 --> 01:08:04.860
And he arose from thence, and cometh into the coast of Judea, by the farthest side of Jordan. And the people resort unto him again, and as he was wont, he taught them again.

01:08:04.860 --> 01:08:18.620
And the Pharisees came to him and asked him, Is it lawful for a man to put away his wife, tempting him? And he answered and said unto them, What did Moses command you?

01:08:18.620 --> 01:08:36.260
And they said, Moses suffered to write a bill of divorcement and to put her away. And Jesus answered and said unto them, For the hardness of your heart he wrote you this precept.

01:08:36.260 --> 01:08:50.220
But from the beginning of the creation God made them male and female. For this cause shall a man leave his father and mother and cleave to his wife.

01:08:50.220 --> 01:09:05.760
And they twain shall be one flesh, so then they are no more twain but one flesh. What therefore God hath joined together, let not man put asunder.

01:09:05.760 --> 01:09:19.980
And in the house his disciples asked him again of the same matter. And he sayeth unto them, Whosoever shall put away his wife and marry another, committeth adultery against her.

01:09:19.980 --> 01:09:32.260
And if a woman shall put away her husband and be married to another, she committeth adultery. And they brought young children to him that he should touch them.

01:09:32.260 --> 01:09:48.660
And his disciples rebuked those that brought them. But when Jesus saw it he was much displeased and said unto them, Suffer the little children to come unto me, and forbid them not.

01:09:48.660 --> 01:10:02.780
For of such is the kingdom of God. Fairly I say unto you, Whosoever shall not receive the kingdom of God, as a little child he shall not enter therein.

01:10:02.780 --> 01:10:23.660
And he took them up in his arms, and put his hands upon them, and blessed them. And when he was gone forth into the way, there came one running, and kneeled to him, and asked him, Good master, what shall I do that I may inherit eternal life?

01:10:23.660 --> 01:10:45.260
And Jesus said unto him, Why callest thou me good? There is none good but one, that is God. Thou knowest the commandments. Do not commit adultery, do not kill, do not steal, do not bear false witness, defraud not, honor thy father and mother.

01:10:45.260 --> 01:11:11.860
And he answered and said unto him, Master, all these have I observed from my youth. Then Jesus, beholding him, loved him, and said unto him, One thing thou lackest, go thy way, sell whatsoever thou hast, and give to the poor, and thou shalt have treasure in heaven.

01:11:11.860 --> 01:11:24.800
And come, take up the cross, and follow me. And he was sad at that saying, and went away grieved, for he had great possessions.

01:11:24.800 --> 01:11:36.340
And Jesus looked round about, and sayeth unto his disciples, How hardly shall they that have riches enter into the kingdom of God?

01:11:36.340 --> 01:12:02.880
And the disciples were astonished at his words. But Jesus answered again, and sayeth unto them, Children, how hard is it for them that trust in riches to enter into the kingdom of God? It is easier for a camel to go through the eye of a needle than for a rich man to enter into the kingdom of God.

01:12:02.880 --> 01:12:22.680
And they were astonished out of measure, saying among themselves, Who then can be saved? And Jesus, looking upon them, sayeth, With men it is impossible, but not with God, for with God all things are possible.

01:12:22.680 --> 01:12:46.140
Then Peter began to say unto him, Lo, we have left all, and have followed thee. And Jesus answered and said, Verily I say unto you, There is no man that hath left house, or brethren, or sisters, or father, or mother, or wife, or children, or lands, for my sake and the gospels.

01:12:46.140 --> 01:13:03.540
But he shall receive in hundredfold, now in this time, houses, and brethren, and sisters, and mothers, and children, and lands, with persecutions, and in the world to come, eternal life.

01:13:03.540 --> 01:13:22.020
But many that are first shall be last, and the last first. And they were in the way going up to Jerusalem, and Jesus went before them, and they were amazed, and as they followed they were afraid.

01:13:22.020 --> 01:13:40.680
And he took again the twelve, and began to tell them what things should happen unto him, saying, Behold, we go up to Jerusalem, and the Son of Man shall be delivered unto the chief priests, and unto the scribes.

01:13:40.680 --> 01:13:54.660
And they shall condemn him to death, and shall deliver him to the Gentiles, and they shall mock him, and shall scourge him, and shall spit upon him, and shall kill him.

01:13:54.660 --> 01:14:11.100
And the third day he shall rise again, and James and John, the sons of Zebedee, came unto him, saying, Master, we would that thou shouldest do for us whatsoever we shall desire.

01:14:11.100 --> 01:14:26.480
And he said unto them, What would ye that I should do for you? They said unto him, Grant unto us that we may sit, one on thy right hand, and the other on thy left hand, in thy glory.

01:14:27.300 --> 01:14:40.460
But Jesus said unto them, Ye know not what ye ask. Can ye drink of the cup that I drink of, and be baptized with the baptism that I am baptized with?

01:14:40.460 --> 01:14:56.710
And they said unto him, We can. And Jesus said unto them, Ye shall indeed drink of the cup that I drink of, and with the baptism that I am baptized with all shall ye be baptized.

01:14:56.710 --> 01:15:08.730
But to sit on my right hand, and on my left hand, is not mine to give. But it shall be given to them for whom it is prepared.

01:15:08.730 --> 01:15:33.410
And when the ten heard it, they began to be much displeased with James and John. But Jesus called them to him, and saith unto them, Ye know that they which are accounted to rule over the Gentiles exercise lordship over them, and their great ones exercise authority upon them.

01:15:33.410 --> 01:15:49.310
But so shall it not be among you, but whosoever will be great among you shall be your minister, and whosoever of you shall be chiefest shall be servant of all.

01:15:49.310 --> 01:15:58.990
For even the Son of Man came not to be ministered unto, but to minister and to give his life a ransom for many.

01:15:58.990 --> 01:16:15.170
And they came to Jericho. And as he went out of Jericho with his disciples, and a great number of people, blind Barnamaeus, the son of Timaeus, sat by the highway side begging.

01:16:15.170 --> 01:16:26.130
And when he heard that it was Jesus of Nazareth, he began to cry out and say, Jesus, thou son of David, have mercy on me.

01:16:26.130 --> 01:16:37.630
And many charged him that he should hold his peace. But he cried the more a great deal, Thou son of David, have mercy on me.

01:16:38.210 --> 01:16:49.810
And Jesus stood still and commanded him to be called. And they called the blind man, saying unto him, Be of good comfort, rise, he calleth thee.

01:16:49.810 --> 01:17:02.170
And he, casting away his garment, rose and came to Jesus. And Jesus answered and said unto him, What wilt thou that I should do unto thee?

01:17:02.530 --> 01:17:16.550
The blind man said unto him, Lord, that I might receive my sight. And Jesus said unto him, Go thy way, thy faith have made thee whole.

01:17:16.550 --> 01:17:23.010
And immediately he received his sight and followed Jesus in the way.

01:17:54.910 --> 01:18:02.790
And when they came nigh to Jerusalem unto Bethphage and Bethany at the Mount of Olives,

01:18:03.130 --> 01:18:10.910
he sendeth forth two of his disciples, and sayeth unto them, Go your way into the village over

01:18:10.910 --> 01:18:20.410
against you, and as soon as ye be entered into it ye shall find a colt tied whereon never man set.

01:18:20.410 --> 01:18:27.670
Loose him and bring him, and if any man say unto you, Why do ye this?

01:18:28.050 --> 01:18:35.230
Say ye that the Lord hath need of him, and straightway he will send him hither.

01:18:35.750 --> 01:18:43.190
They went their way and found the colt by the door without a place where two ways met,

01:18:43.190 --> 01:18:51.430
and they loosed him. And certain of them that stood there said unto them, What do ye loosing

01:18:51.430 --> 01:18:58.610
the colt? And they said unto them, Even as Jesus had commanded, and they let them go.

01:18:59.190 --> 01:19:06.210
And they brought the colt to Jesus and cast their garments on him, and he set upon him.

01:19:06.770 --> 01:19:12.770
And many spread their garments in the way, and others cut down branches off the trees

01:19:12.770 --> 01:19:21.290
and strawed them in the way. And they that went before and they that followed cried, saying,

01:19:21.670 --> 01:19:29.550
Hosanna, blessed is he that cometh in the name of the Lord. Blessed be the kingdom of our father

01:19:29.550 --> 01:19:39.250
David that cometh in the name of the Lord. Hosanna in the highest. And Jesus entered into Jerusalem

01:19:39.250 --> 01:19:47.950
and into the temple, and when he had looked round about upon all things, and now the even

01:19:47.950 --> 01:19:57.430
tide was come, he went out on to Bethany with the twelve. And on the morrow, when they were come

01:19:57.430 --> 01:20:06.910
from Bethany, he was hungry, and seeing a fig tree afar off having leaves, he came. If happily he

01:20:06.910 --> 01:20:17.110
might find anything thereon. And when he came to it, he found nothing but leaves, for the time of

01:20:17.110 --> 01:20:26.590
figs was not yet. And Jesus answered and said unto it, No man eat fruit of thee hereafter forever.

01:20:27.370 --> 01:20:35.690
And his disciples heard it, and they come to Jerusalem. And Jesus went into the temple and

01:20:35.690 --> 01:20:43.050
began to cast out them that sold and bought in the temple, and overthrew the tables of the money

01:20:43.050 --> 01:20:51.590
changers and the seats of them that sold doves, and would not suffer that any man should carry

01:20:51.590 --> 01:21:01.430
any vessel through the temple. And he taught, saying unto them, Is it not written, My house shall

01:21:01.430 --> 01:21:12.190
be called of all nations the house of prayer? But ye have made it a den of thieves. And the scribes

01:21:12.190 --> 01:21:20.170
and chief priests heard it, and saw how they might destroy him, for they feared him, because all the

01:21:20.170 --> 01:21:30.170
people was astonished at his doctrine. And when even was come, he went out of the city, and in the

01:21:30.170 --> 01:21:39.750
morning, as they passed by, they saw the fig tree dried up from the roots. And Peter, calling to

01:21:39.750 --> 01:21:47.770
remembrance, saith unto him, Master, behold the fig tree, which thou cursed, is withered away.

01:21:48.550 --> 01:21:56.130
And Jesus answering, saith unto him, Have faith in God. For verily I say unto you,

01:21:56.130 --> 01:22:03.910
that whosoever shall say unto this mountain, Be thou removed, and be thou cast into the sea,

01:22:04.170 --> 01:22:10.770
and shall not doubt in his heart, but shall believe that those things which he saith shall

01:22:10.770 --> 01:22:20.190
come to pass, he shall have whatsoever he saith. Therefore I say unto you, what things so ever ye

01:22:20.190 --> 01:22:29.290
desire, when ye pray, believe that ye receive them, and ye shall have them. And when ye stand

01:22:29.290 --> 01:22:38.330
praying, forgive if ye have ought against any, that your father also which is in heaven may forgive

01:22:38.330 --> 01:22:48.350
you your trespasses. But if ye do not forgive, neither will your father which is in heaven

01:22:48.350 --> 01:22:58.370
forgive your trespasses. And they came again to Jerusalem, and as he was walking in the temple,

01:22:58.710 --> 01:23:06.630
there come to him the chief priests, and scribes, and the elders, and say unto him, By what authority

01:23:06.630 --> 01:23:13.570
doest thou these things? And who gave thee this authority to do these things? And Jesus answered

01:23:13.570 --> 01:23:22.170
and said unto them, I will also ask of you one question, and answer me, and I will tell you by

01:23:22.170 --> 01:23:31.470
what authority I do these things. The baptism of John, was it from heaven or of men? Answer me.

01:23:32.250 --> 01:23:40.030
And they reasoned with themselves, saying, If we shall say from heaven, he will say, Why then

01:23:40.030 --> 01:23:49.970
did ye not believe him? But if we shall say of men, they feared the people, for all men counted John

01:23:49.970 --> 01:24:00.490
that he was a prophet indeed. And they answered and said unto Jesus, We cannot tell. And Jesus

01:24:00.490 --> 01:24:08.770
answering sayeth unto them, Neither do I tell you by what authority I do these things.

01:24:09.650 --> 01:24:18.430
And he began to speak unto them by parables. A certain man planted a vineyard,

01:24:18.750 --> 01:24:27.870
and set an hedge about it, and digged a place for the wine vat, and built a tower, and let it out

01:24:27.870 --> 01:24:35.310
to husband men, and went into a far country. And at the season he sent to the husband men,

01:24:35.310 --> 01:24:41.370
a servant that he might receive from the husband men of the fruit of the vineyard.

01:24:41.550 --> 01:24:48.470
And they caught him and beat him, and sent him away empty. And again he sent unto them

01:24:48.470 --> 01:24:55.890
another servant, and at him they cast stones and wounded him in the head, and sent him away

01:24:55.890 --> 01:25:06.070
shamefully handled. And again he sent another, and him they killed, and many others beating some

01:25:06.070 --> 01:25:15.990
and killing some. Having yet therefore one son, his well-beloved, he sent him also last unto them,

01:25:15.990 --> 01:25:25.370
saying, They will reverence my son. But those husband men said among themselves, This is the

01:25:26.170 --> 01:25:35.190
come, let us kill him, and the inheritance shall be ours. And they took him and killed him, and cast

01:25:35.190 --> 01:25:43.950
him out of the vineyard. What shall therefore the lord of the vineyard do? He will come and destroy

01:25:43.950 --> 01:25:51.650
the husband men, and will give the vineyard unto others. And have ye not read this scripture,

01:25:51.650 --> 01:25:58.550
The stone which the builders rejected is become the head of the corner.

01:25:59.430 --> 01:26:07.370
This was the lord's doing, and it is marvelous in our eyes. And they sought to lay hold on him,

01:26:07.630 --> 01:26:15.750
but feared the people, for they knew that he had spoken the parable against them. And they left him,

01:26:15.750 --> 01:26:23.430
and went their way. And they send unto him certain of the Pharisees, and of the Herodians,

01:26:23.510 --> 01:26:31.450
to catch him in his words. And when they will come, they say unto him, Master, we know that

01:26:31.450 --> 01:26:39.290
thou art true, and carest for no man, for thou regardest not the person of men, but teachest

01:26:39.290 --> 01:26:50.330
the way of God in truth. Is it lawful to give tribute to Caesar, or not? Shall we give,

01:26:50.530 --> 01:26:58.310
or shall we not give? But he, knowing their hypocrisy, said unto them, Why tempt ye me?

01:26:58.990 --> 01:27:06.370
Bring me a penny, that I may see it. And they brought it. And he sayeth unto them, Whose is

01:27:06.370 --> 01:27:16.730
this image and superscription? And they said unto him, Caesar's. And Jesus answering said unto them,

01:27:17.090 --> 01:27:26.550
Render to Caesar the things that are Caesar's, and to God the things that are God's. And they

01:27:26.550 --> 01:27:35.550
marveled at him. Then come unto him the Sadducees, which say there is no resurrection.

01:27:35.550 --> 01:27:44.490
And they asked him, saying, Master, Moses wrote unto us, If a man's brother die, and leave his

01:27:44.490 --> 01:27:51.810
wife behind, and leave no children, that his brother should take his wife, and raise up seed

01:27:51.810 --> 01:28:02.670
unto his brother. Now there were seven brethren, and the first took a wife, and dying left no seed.

01:28:02.670 --> 01:28:11.170
And the second took her and died, neither left he any seed. And the third likewise, and the seven

01:28:11.170 --> 01:28:20.590
had her, and left no seed. Last of all the woman died also. In the resurrection therefore, when

01:28:20.590 --> 01:28:29.750
they shall rise, whose wife shall she be of them? For the seven had her two wife. And Jesus answering

01:28:29.750 --> 01:28:39.250
said unto them, Do ye not therefore err, because ye know not the scriptures, neither the power of

01:28:39.250 --> 01:28:47.010
God? For when they shall rise from the dead, they neither marry nor are given in marriage,

01:28:47.450 --> 01:28:55.410
but are as the angels which are in heaven. And as touching the dead that they rise,

01:28:55.410 --> 01:29:02.710
have ye not read in the book of Moses, how in the bush God spake unto him, saying,

01:29:03.210 --> 01:29:13.370
I am the God of Abraham, and the God of Isaac, and the God of Jacob? He is not the God of the dead,

01:29:13.730 --> 01:29:22.030
but the God of the living. Ye therefore do greatly err. And one of the scribes came, and having heard

01:29:22.030 --> 01:29:30.010
them reasoning together, and perceiving that he had answered them well, asked him, Which is the

01:29:30.010 --> 01:29:38.530
first commandment of all? And Jesus answered him, The first of all the commandments is, Here, O Israel,

01:29:39.190 --> 01:29:47.750
the Lord our God is one Lord, and thou shalt love the Lord thy God with all thy heart, and with all

01:29:47.750 --> 01:29:56.990
thy soul, and with all thy mind, and with all thy strength. This is the first commandment. And the

01:29:56.990 --> 01:30:05.910
second is like, namely this, thou shalt love thy neighbor as thyself. There is none other commandment

01:30:06.490 --> 01:30:14.050
greater than these. And the scribe said unto him, Well, master, thou hast said the truth,

01:30:14.050 --> 01:30:20.950
for there is one God, and there is none other but he, and to love him with all the heart,

01:30:21.090 --> 01:30:27.610
and with all the understanding, and with all the soul, and with all the strength, and to love

01:30:27.930 --> 01:30:37.590
his neighbor as himself is more than all whole burnt offerings and sacrifices. And when Jesus

01:30:37.590 --> 01:30:44.930
saw that he answered discreetly, he said unto him, Thou art not far from the kingdom of God,

01:30:45.330 --> 01:30:55.110
and no man after that darest ask him any question. And Jesus answered and said, While he taught in

01:30:55.110 --> 01:31:02.650
the temple, How say the scribes that Christ is the son of David? For David himself said by the Holy

01:31:02.650 --> 01:31:11.590
Ghost, The Lord said to my Lord, Sit thou on my right hand, till I make thine enemies thy footstool.

01:31:12.030 --> 01:31:20.710
David therefore himself calleth him Lord, and whence is he then his son? And the common people heard

01:31:20.710 --> 01:31:29.190
him gladly, and he said unto them in his doctrine, Beware of the scribes which love to go in long

01:31:29.190 --> 01:31:36.870
clothing, and love salutations in the market places, and the chief seats in the synagogues,

01:31:37.210 --> 01:31:45.730
and the uppermost rooms at feast. Which devour widows' houses, and for a pretense make long

01:31:45.730 --> 01:31:54.990
prayers, these shall receive greater damnation. And Jesus sat over against the treasury, and beheld

01:31:54.990 --> 01:32:03.410
how the people cast money into the treasury, and many that were rich cast in much. And there came

01:32:03.410 --> 01:32:13.610
a certain poor widow, and she threw in two mites, which make a farthing. And he called unto him his

01:32:13.610 --> 01:32:22.470
disciples, and sayeth unto them, Verily I say unto you, That this poor widow has cast more in than

01:32:22.470 --> 01:32:31.370
all they which have cast into the treasury. For all they did cast in of their abundance,

01:32:31.830 --> 01:32:40.610
but she of her want did cast in all that she had, even all her living.

01:33:42.590 --> 01:34:06.090
And as he set upon the Mount of Olives over against the temple, Peter and James and John and Andrew asked him privately, Tell us, when shall these things be, and what shall be the sign when all these things shall be fulfilled?

01:34:06.090 --> 01:34:20.420
And Jesus answering them began to say, Take heed, least any man deceive you, for many shall come in my name, saying, I am Christ, and shall deceive many.

01:34:20.420 --> 01:34:49.900
And when ye shall hear of wars and rumors of wars, be ye not troubled, for such things must needs be. But the end shall not be yet, for nation shall rise against nation and kingdom against kingdom, and there shall be earthquakes in divers places, and there shall be famines and troubles. These are the beginnings of sorrows.

01:34:49.900 --> 01:35:08.120
But take heed to yourselves, for they shall deliver you up to councils, and in synagogues ye shall be beaten, and ye shall be brought before rulers and kings for my sake, for a testimony against them.

01:35:08.120 --> 01:35:36.060
And the gospel must first be published among all nations, but when they shall lead you and deliver you up, take no thought beforehand what ye shall say, neither do ye premeditate, but whatsoever shall be given you in that hour that speak ye, for it is not ye that speak, but the Holy Ghost.

01:35:36.060 --> 01:35:48.900
Now the brother shall betray the brother to death, and the father the son, and children shall rise up against their parents, and shall cause them to be put to death.

01:35:48.900 --> 01:36:00.460
And ye shall be hated of all men for my name's sake, but he that shall endure unto the end, the same shall be saved.

01:36:00.460 --> 01:36:13.700
But when ye shall see the abomination of the desolation spoken of by Daniel the prophet standing where it ought not, let him that readeth understand.

01:36:13.700 --> 01:36:28.800
Then let them that be in Judea flee to the mountains, and let him that is on the housetop not go down into the house, neither enter therein to take anything out of his house.

01:36:28.800 --> 01:36:42.680
And let him that is in the field not turn back again, for to take up his garment, but woe to them that are with child, and to them that give suck in those days.

01:36:42.680 --> 01:37:00.460
And pray ye that your flight be not in the winter, for in those days shall be affliction, such as was not from the beginning of the creation which God created unto this time, and neither shall be.

01:37:00.460 --> 01:37:13.900
And accept that the Lord had shortened those days, no flesh should be saved, but for the elect's sake, whom he hath chosen, he hath shortened the days.

01:37:13.900 --> 01:37:35.920
And then, if any man shall say to you, Lo, here is Christ, or Lo, he is there, believe him not, for false Christs and false prophets shall rise, and shall show signs and wonders to seduce, if it were possible even the elect.

01:37:35.920 --> 01:37:57.000
But take ye heed, behold, I have foretold you all things, but in those days, after that tribulation, the sun shall be darkened, and the moon shall not give her light, and the stars of heaven shall fall, and the powers that are in heaven shall be shaken.

01:37:57.000 --> 01:38:18.960
And then shall they see the Son of Man coming in the clouds with great power and glory, and then shall he send his angels, and shall gather together his elect from the four winds, from the uttermost part of the earth to the uttermost part of heaven.

01:38:18.960 --> 01:38:29.940
Now learn a parable of the fig tree, when her branch is yet tender and putteth forth leaves, ye know that summer is near.

01:38:29.940 --> 01:38:48.440
So ye in like manner, when ye see these things come to pass, know that it is nigh even at the doors. Verily, I say unto you, that this generation shall not pass till all these things be done.

01:38:48.440 --> 01:39:05.800
Heaven and earth shall pass away, but my words shall not pass away. But of that day and that hour knoweth no man. No, not the angels which are in heaven, neither the Son, but the Father.

01:39:05.800 --> 01:39:26.680
Take ye he, watch and pray, for ye know not when the time is. For the Son of Man is as a man taking a far journey, who left his house, and gave authority to his servants, and to every man his work, and commanded the porter to watch.

01:39:26.680 --> 01:39:49.460
Watch ye therefore, for ye know not when the master of the house cometh. At even, or at midnight, or at the cock crowing, or in the morning, lest coming suddenly he find you sleeping. And what I say unto you, I say unto all, watch.

01:39:50.420 --> 01:40:06.120
After two days was the feast of the Passover, and of unleavened bread. And the chief priests and the scribes sought how they might take him by craft, and put him to death.

01:40:06.120 --> 01:40:25.380
But they said, Not on the feast day, lest there be an uproar of the people. And being in Bethany, in the house of Simon the leper, as he said at me, there came a woman, having an alabaster box of ointment of spikenard, very precious.

01:40:25.380 --> 01:40:46.480
And she broke the box, and poured it on his head. And there were some that had indignation within themselves, and said, Why was this waste of the ointment made? For it might have been sold for more than three hundred pence, and had been given to the poor.

01:40:46.480 --> 01:41:08.760
And they murmured against her. And Jesus said, Let her alone. Why trouble ye her? She hath wrought a good work on me. For ye have the poor with you always. And when soever ye will, ye may do them good. But me ye have not always.

01:41:08.760 --> 01:41:29.600
She hath done what she could. She has come aforehand to anoint my body to the burying. Verily I say unto you, Where soever this gospel shall be preached throughout the whole world, this also that she hath done shall be spoken of for a memorial of her.

01:41:29.600 --> 01:41:49.220
And Judas Iscariot, one of the twelve, went unto the chief priest to betray him unto them. And when they heard it, they were glad and promised to give him money. And he sought how he might conveniently betray him.

01:41:49.220 --> 01:42:03.540
And the first day of unleavened bread, when they killed the Passover, his disciples said unto him, Where wilt thou that we go and prepare that thou mayest eat the Passover?

01:42:03.540 --> 01:42:32.480
And he sendeth forth two of his disciples, and saith unto them, Go ye into the city, and there shall meet you a man bearing a pitcher of water. Follow him. And where soever he shall go in, say ye to the good man of the house, the master saith, Where is the guest chamber where I shall eat the Passover with my disciples?

01:42:32.480 --> 01:42:50.800
And he will show you a large upper room, furnished and prepared, there make ready for us. And his disciples went forth, and came into the city, and found as he had said unto them. And they made ready the Passover.

01:42:50.800 --> 01:43:07.160
And in the evening he cometh with the twelve. And as they sat and did eat, Jesus said, Verily, I say unto you, One of you which eateth with me shall betray me.

01:43:07.160 --> 01:43:25.880
And they began to be sorrowful, and to say unto him one by one, Is it I? And another said, Is it I? And he answered and said unto them, It is one of the twelve that dippeth with me in the dish.

01:43:25.880 --> 01:43:43.340
The son of man indeed goeth, as it is written of him, but woe to that man by whom the son of man is betrayed. Good were it for that man if he had never been born.

01:43:43.340 --> 01:44:03.660
And as they did eat, Jesus took bread, and blessed and broke it, and gave it to them, and said, Take, eat, this is my body. And he took the cup, and when he had given thanks, he gave it to them, and they all drank of it.

01:44:03.660 --> 01:44:24.740
And he said unto them, This is my blood of the New Testament, which is shed for many. Verily, I say unto you, I will drink no more of the fruit of the vine until that day that I drink it new in the kingdom of God.

01:44:24.740 --> 01:44:46.100
And when they had sung a hymn, they went out into the Mount of Olives. And Jesus sayeth unto them, All ye shall be offended because of me this night, for it is written, I will smite the shepherd, and the sheep shall be scattered.

01:44:46.100 --> 01:44:58.420
But after that I am risen, I will go before you in to Galilee. But Peter said unto him, Although all shall be offended, yet will not I.

01:44:58.420 --> 01:45:23.620
And Jesus sayeth unto him, Verily I say unto thee, that this day, even in this night, before the cock crow twice thou shalt deny me thrice. But his fate the more vehemently, if I should die with thee, I will not deny thee in any wise. Likewise also said they all.

01:45:23.620 --> 01:45:40.900
And they came to a place which was named Gethsemane. And he sayeth to his disciples, Sit ye here while I shall pray. And he taketh with him Peter, and James, and John, and began to be sore, amazed, and to be very heavy.

01:45:40.900 --> 01:45:59.840
And sayeth unto them, My soul is exceeding sorrowful unto death, tarry ye here and watch. And he went forward a little, and fell on the ground, and prayed that if it were possible, the hour might pass from him.

01:45:59.840 --> 01:46:11.720
And he said, Abba Father, all things are possible unto thee. Take away this cup from me. Nevertheless, not what I will, but what thou wilt.

01:46:11.720 --> 01:46:30.680
And he cometh, and findeth them sleeping, and sayeth unto Peter, Simon, sleepest thou? Couldest thou not watch one hour? Watch ye and pray. Lest ye enter into temptation, the spirit truly is ready, but the flesh is weak.

01:46:30.680 --> 01:46:45.580
And again he went away, and prayed, and spake the same words. And when he returned, he found them asleep, for their eyes were heavy. Neither whisked they what to answer him.

01:46:45.580 --> 01:47:00.800
And he cometh the third time, and sayeth unto them, Sleep on now, and take your rest. It is enough. The hour is come. Behold, the Son of Man is betrayed into the hands of sinners.

01:47:00.800 --> 01:47:20.680
Rise up, let us go. Lo, he that betrayeth me is at hand. And immediately while he yet spake cometh Judas, one of the twelve, and with him a great multitude with swords and staves from the chief priests and scribes and the elders.

01:47:20.680 --> 01:47:32.560
And he that betrayed him had given them a token, saying, Whomsoever I shall kiss, that same is he. Take him, and lead him away safely.

01:47:32.560 --> 01:47:46.000
And as soon as he was come, he goeth straightway to him, and sayeth, Master, Master, and kissed him. And they laid their hands on him, and took him.

01:47:46.000 --> 01:48:04.020
And one of them that stood by drew a sword, and smote a servant of the high priest, and cut off his ear. And Jesus answered and said unto them, Are ye come out as against a thief with swords and with staves to take me?

01:48:04.020 --> 01:48:25.360
I was daily with you in the temple teaching, and ye took me not. But the scriptures must be fulfilled. And they all forsook him and fled. And there followed him a certain young man having a linen cloth cast about his naked body.

01:48:25.360 --> 01:48:43.720
And the young men laid hold on him, and he left the linen cloth and fled from them naked. And they led Jesus away to the high priest, and with him were assembled all the chief priests and the elders and the scribes.

01:48:43.720 --> 01:49:02.620
And Peter followed him afar off, even into the palace of the high priest. And he sat with the servants and warmed himself at the fire. And the chief priests and all the councils sought for witness against Jesus, to put him to death and found none.

01:49:02.620 --> 01:49:24.680
For many bare false witness against him, but their witness agreed not together. And there arose certain, and bare false witness against him, saying, We heard him say, I will destroy this temple that is made with hands, and within three days I will build another made without hands.

01:49:24.680 --> 01:49:43.280
But neither so did their witness agree together. And the high priest stood up in the midst and asked Jesus, saying, Answerest thou nothing? What is it which these witness against thee? But he held his peace and answered nothing.

01:49:43.280 --> 01:50:02.580
Again the high priest asked him and said unto him, Art thou the Christ, the Son of the Blessed? And Jesus said, I am. And ye shall see the Son of Man sitting on the right hand of power and coming in the clouds of heaven.

01:50:02.580 --> 01:50:18.560
Then the high priest rent his clothes and sayeth, What need we any further witnesses? Ye have heard the blasphemy? What think ye? And they all condemned him to be guilty of death.

01:50:18.560 --> 01:50:31.880
And some began to spit on him and to cover his face and to buffet him and to say unto him, Prophesy. And the servants did strike him with the palms of their hands.

01:50:31.880 --> 01:50:49.160
And as Peter was beneath in the palace, there cometh one of the maids of the high priest. And when she saw Peter warming himself, she looked upon him and said, And thou also wast with Jesus of Nazareth?

01:50:49.160 --> 01:51:00.680
But he denied, saying, I know not, neither understand I what thou sayest. And he went out into the porch and the cock crew.

01:51:00.680 --> 01:51:20.740
And a maid saw him again and began to say to them that stood by, This is one of them. And he denied it again. And a little after, they that stood by said again to Peter, Surely thou art one of them, for thou art a Galilean.

01:51:20.740 --> 01:51:31.780
And thy speech agreeeth thereto. But he began to curse and to swear, saying, I know not this man of whom ye speak. And the second time the cock crew.

01:51:33.160 --> 01:51:46.580
And Peter called to mind the word that Jesus said unto him, Before the cock crow twice thou shalt deny me thrice. And when he thought thereon, he wept.

01:52:20.940 --> 01:52:28.880
And straightway in the morning the chief priest held a consultation with the elders and the scribes and the whole council,

01:52:29.440 --> 01:52:35.200
and bound Jesus, and carried him away, and delivered him to Pilate.

01:52:35.200 --> 01:52:39.760
And Pilate asked him, Art thou the king of the Jews?

01:52:39.880 --> 01:52:43.520
And he answering said unto them, Thou sayest it.

01:52:44.480 --> 01:52:50.720
And the chief priest accused him of many things, but he answered nothing.

01:52:51.220 --> 01:52:55.080
And Pilate asked him again, saying, Answers thou nothing?

01:52:55.740 --> 01:52:59.040
Behold, how many things they witness against thee!

01:52:59.540 --> 01:53:04.320
But Jesus yet answered nothing, so that Pilate marveled.

01:53:04.320 --> 01:53:11.420
Now at that feast he released unto them one prisoner, whom soever they desired.

01:53:11.960 --> 01:53:22.260
And there was one named Barabbas, which lay bound with them, that had made insurrection against him,

01:53:22.440 --> 01:53:25.960
who had committed murder in the insurrection.

01:53:25.960 --> 01:53:34.500
And the multitude, crying aloud, began to desire him to do as he had ever done unto them.

01:53:34.800 --> 01:53:42.720
But Pilate answered them, saying, Will ye that I release unto you the king of the Jews?

01:53:43.240 --> 01:53:47.760
For he knew that the chief priest had delivered him for envy.

01:53:48.240 --> 01:53:55.260
But the chief priest moved the people, that he should rather release Barabbas unto them.

01:53:55.900 --> 01:54:07.660
And Pilate answered and said again unto them, What will ye then that I shall do unto him whom ye call the king of the Jews?

01:54:07.960 --> 01:54:11.100
And they cried out again, Crucify him.

01:54:11.480 --> 01:54:15.420
Then Pilate said unto them, Why, what evil hath he done?

01:54:15.720 --> 01:54:20.000
And they cried out the more exceedingly, Crucify him.

01:54:20.000 --> 01:54:25.540
And so Pilate, willing to content the people, released Barabbas unto them,

01:54:25.920 --> 01:54:30.840
and delivered Jesus when he had scourged him to be crucified.

01:54:31.480 --> 01:54:38.320
And the soldiers led him away into the hall, called Praetorium.

01:54:38.920 --> 01:54:47.240
And they called together the whole band, and they clothed him with purple, and plaited a crown of thorns,

01:54:47.240 --> 01:54:54.000
and put it upon his head, and began to salute him, Hail, King of the Jews!

01:54:54.380 --> 01:55:03.960
And they smote him on the head with a reed, and did spit upon him, and bowing their knees worshiped him.

01:55:04.240 --> 01:55:12.500
And when they had mocked him, they took off the purple from him, and put his own clothes on him,

01:55:12.500 --> 01:55:16.000
and led him out to crucify him.

01:55:16.200 --> 01:55:24.220
And they compel one, Simon, a Serenian, who passed by, coming out of the country,

01:55:24.720 --> 01:55:29.780
the father of Alexander and Rufus, to bear his cross.

01:55:30.080 --> 01:55:38.320
And they bring him unto the place, Golgotha, which is being interpreted the place of a skull.

01:55:38.880 --> 01:55:46.640
And they gave him to drink wine, mingled with myrrh, but he received it not.

01:55:46.960 --> 01:55:53.620
And when they had crucified him, they parted his garments, casting lots upon them,

01:55:53.720 --> 01:55:56.160
what every man should take.

01:55:56.520 --> 01:56:00.420
And it was the third hour, and they crucified him.

01:56:00.420 --> 01:56:08.840
And the superscription of his accusation was written over the King of the Jews.

01:56:09.480 --> 01:56:16.240
And with him they crucified two thieves, the one on his right hand, and the other on his left.

01:56:16.800 --> 01:56:23.180
And the scripture was fulfilled which saith, and he was numbered with the transgressors.

01:56:23.180 --> 01:56:29.120
And they that passed by railed on him, wagging their heads and saying,

01:56:29.720 --> 01:56:33.760
Ah, thou that destroyest the temple and buildest it in three days,

01:56:34.320 --> 01:56:37.440
save thyself and come down from the cross.

01:56:38.120 --> 01:56:44.460
Likewise also the chief priests, mocking, said among themselves with the scribes,

01:56:44.740 --> 01:56:48.660
he saved others, himself he cannot save.

01:56:49.300 --> 01:56:57.260
Let Christ the King of Israel descend now from the cross that we may see and believe.

01:56:57.880 --> 01:57:02.720
And they that were crucified with him reviled him.

01:57:03.040 --> 01:57:11.640
And when the sixth hour was come, there was darkness over the whole land until the ninth hour.

01:57:12.240 --> 01:57:17.060
And at the ninth hour Jesus cried with a loud voice saying,

01:57:17.940 --> 01:57:23.160
Eloi, Eloi lama sabachthani, which is being interpreted,

01:57:23.700 --> 01:57:28.960
My God, my God, why hast thou forsaken me?

01:57:29.520 --> 01:57:35.780
And some of them that stood by when they heard it said, Behold, he calleth Elias.

01:57:36.360 --> 01:57:44.160
And one ran and filled a sponge full of vinegar and put it on a reed and gave him to drink,

01:57:44.160 --> 01:57:49.680
saying, Let alone, let us see whether Elias will come to take him down.

01:57:50.040 --> 01:57:54.860
And Jesus cried with a loud voice and gave up the ghost.

01:57:55.860 --> 01:58:00.320
And the veil of the temple was rent entwined from the top to the bottom.

01:58:00.640 --> 01:58:08.360
And when the centurion which stood over against him saw that he so cried out and gave up the ghost,

01:58:08.920 --> 01:58:13.400
he said, Truly, this man was the Son of God.

01:58:13.910 --> 01:58:22.260
There were also women looking on afar off, among whom was Mary Magdalene and Mary,

01:58:22.400 --> 01:58:30.440
the mother of James, the less, and Jose's and Salome, who also when he was in Galilee followed

01:58:30.440 --> 01:58:38.320
him and ministered unto him, and many other women which came up with him unto Jerusalem.

01:58:38.320 --> 01:58:46.700
And now, when the even was come, because it was the preparation that is the day before the Sabbath,

01:58:47.700 --> 01:58:55.340
Joseph of Aramaothea, an honorable counselor, which also waited for the kingdom of God,

01:58:55.400 --> 01:59:01.920
came and went in boldly unto Pilate and craved the body of Jesus.

01:59:02.700 --> 01:59:09.220
And Pilate marveled if he were already dead, and calling unto him the centurion,

01:59:09.620 --> 01:59:13.200
he asked him whether he had been any while dead.

01:59:13.560 --> 01:59:19.060
And when he knew it of the centurion, he gave the body to Joseph.

01:59:20.020 --> 01:59:30.400
And he bought fine linen and took him down and wrapped him in the linen, and laid him in a

01:59:30.400 --> 01:59:34.920
rock, and rolled a stone on to the door of the sepulcher.

01:59:36.120 --> 01:59:41.740
And Mary Magdalene and Mary, the mother of Joseus, beheld where he was laid.

01:59:43.500 --> 01:59:51.320
And when the Sabbath was passed, Mary Magdalene and Mary, the mother of James and Salome,

01:59:51.600 --> 01:59:56.660
had bought sweet spices that they might come and anoint him.

01:59:56.660 --> 02:00:01.340
And very early in the morning, the first day of the week, they came

02:00:01.860 --> 02:00:07.440
unto the sepulcher at the rising of the sun. And they said among themselves,

02:00:07.920 --> 02:00:12.500
Who shall roll away the stone from the door of the sepulcher?

02:00:13.100 --> 02:00:19.560
And when they looked, they saw that the stone was rolled away, for it was very great.

02:00:19.560 --> 02:00:26.640
And entering into the sepulcher, they saw a young man sitting on the right side,

02:00:26.780 --> 02:00:31.400
clothed in a long white garment, and they were affrighted.

02:00:32.560 --> 02:00:39.900
And he saith unto them, Be not affrighted, ye seek Jesus of Nazareth, which was crucified.

02:00:40.280 --> 02:00:46.720
He is risen, he is not here. Behold the place where they laid him.

02:00:47.520 --> 02:00:55.260
But go your way, tell his disciples and Peter, that he goeth before you into Galilee.

02:00:55.700 --> 02:01:00.020
There shall ye see him, as he said unto you.

02:01:00.500 --> 02:01:06.580
And they went out quickly and fled from the sepulcher, for they trembled and were amazed.

02:01:06.860 --> 02:01:11.240
Neither said they anything to any man, for they were afraid.

02:01:11.760 --> 02:01:15.540
Now when Jesus was risen early the first day of the week,

02:01:15.940 --> 02:01:21.640
he appeared first to Mary Magdalene, out of whom he had cast seven devils.

02:01:22.480 --> 02:01:28.500
And she went and told them that had been with him as they mourned and wept.

02:01:29.080 --> 02:01:37.200
And they, when they heard that he was alive and had been seen of her, believed not.

02:01:38.000 --> 02:01:45.900
After that he appeared in another form unto two of them, as they walked and went into the country.

02:01:46.420 --> 02:01:51.760
And they went and told it unto the residue, neither believed they them.

02:01:52.460 --> 02:02:00.460
Afterward he appeared unto the eleven as they sat at meet, and upbraided them with their unbelief

02:02:00.460 --> 02:02:07.100
and heartness of heart, because they believed not them which had seen him after he was risen.

02:02:07.200 --> 02:02:14.940
And he said unto them, Go ye into all the world and preach the gospel to every creature.

02:02:15.620 --> 02:02:20.200
He that believeth and is baptized shall be saved.

02:02:20.720 --> 02:02:23.740
But he that believeth not shall be damned.

02:02:24.380 --> 02:02:28.060
And these signs shall follow them that believe.

02:02:28.880 --> 02:02:34.500
In my name shall they cast out devils. They shall speak with new tongues.

02:02:34.500 --> 02:02:41.380
They shall take up serpents, and if they drink any deadly thing, it shall not hurt them.

02:02:41.600 --> 02:02:46.140
They shall lay hands on the sick, and they shall recover.

02:02:47.060 --> 02:02:54.900
So then, after the Lord had spoken unto them, he was received up into heaven and sat

02:02:54.900 --> 02:03:01.740
on the right hand of God. And they went forth and preached everywhere the Lord,

02:03:01.740 --> 02:03:09.460
working with them and confirming the word with signs following. Amen.
